From: Alexander Gordeev <agordeev@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 18 Feb 2014 11:07:53 +0100
Subject: [PATCH v2 24/31] bnx2: Use pci_enable_msix_range() instead of
 pci_enable_msix()
Patch-mainline: v3.15-rc1

Git-commit: f2a2dfeb9431325b40317c9733d8a9536001d15a
References: bsc#908686 FATE#317538


As result of deprecation of MSI-X/MSI enablement functions
pci_enable_msix() and pci_enable_msi_block() all drivers
using these two interfaces need to be updated to use the
new pci_enable_msi_range() and pci_enable_msix_range()
interfaces.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Gordeev <agordeev@redhat.com>
Cc: Michael Chan <mchan@broadcom.com>
Cc: netdev@vger.kernel.org
Cc: linux-pci@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Cho, Yu-Chen <acho@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2.c |   15 ++++-----------
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/bnx2.c
@@ -6205,7 +6205,7 @@ bnx2_free_irq(struct bnx2 *bp)
 static void
 bnx2_enable_msix(struct bnx2 *bp, int msix_vecs)
 {
-	int i, total_vecs, rc;
+	int i, total_vecs;
 	struct msix_entry msix_ent[BNX2_MAX_MSIX_VEC];
 	struct net_device *dev = bp->dev;
 	const int len = sizeof(bp->irq_tbl[0].name);
@@ -6228,16 +6228,9 @@ bnx2_enable_msix(struct bnx2 *bp, int ms
 #ifdef BCM_CNIC
 	total_vecs++;
 #endif
-	rc = -ENOSPC;
-	while (total_vecs >= BNX2_MIN_MSIX_VEC) {
-		rc = pci_enable_msix(bp->pdev, msix_ent, total_vecs);
-		if (rc <= 0)
-			break;
-		if (rc > 0)
-			total_vecs = rc;
-	}
-
-	if (rc != 0)
+	total_vecs = pci_enable_msix_range(bp->pdev, msix_ent,
+					   BNX2_MIN_MSIX_VEC, total_vecs);
+	if (total_vecs < 0)
 		return;
 
 	msix_vecs = total_vecs;
